        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8619",
        "content": "Through the hall then went the Helmings' Lady, to younger and older everywhere carried the cup, till come the moment when the ring graced queen, the royal hearted, to Beowulf bore the beaker of mead. She greeted the Geats' lord, God she thanked, in wisdom's words, that her will was granted, that at last on a hero her hope could lean for comfort in terrors.",
