        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8619",
        "content": "Then laughed his heart; for the monster was minded, ere morn should dawn, savage, to sever the soul of each, life from body, since lusty banquet waited his will!",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-low_s-slow_e-normal",
